comment: 451 billion cells: 5 smack pack(s) or vial(s) of liquid yeast, or 23 gram(s) of dry yeast.
split between so5 and northwest, will probably dry hop one with with something other than citra
IBUs are calculated low, but 8 oz of hops will be sitting in the wort while I slowly run through my chiller, will note bitterness when I taste in 4 weeks or so.

used was too small amount of strike watrer, should have been 9, used 7. also, got stuck twice, so i had to blow, maybe that cause a channel?  maybe my pH was off? any how, 7 gallons strike, 164 strike, added it qt cool to get to 162, 148 mash, 146 at the end, 90 minute mash, mashed out to 175, sparged with 178 water, pulled 12.25 gallons, added 1 distilled, 1052 OG at 66, hop stand while running through chiller, filled each a bit over 5, the short one went first so didnt get as long a hop stand.
9/15 s05 was finished so dry hopped with 4 oz citra, wyeast northwest ale was still chugging along, left it be.
kegged s05, FG was 1.004, smelled nice
